The paper deals with the collective behavior of populations and the effect of communication noise on their ability to solve a task. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), which deals with the study of systems composed of multiple interacting agents. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of computational models to study the behavior of populations, which may also place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also presents a lower bound on the performance of the communication scheme, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), which deal with the analysis and optimization of algorithms and computational models.
